    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez**, whose score of 82.97 makes him our premier start against Lorenzen. The combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park (+14%) and the premium second-spot in the order drives his elite efficiency. We are also aggressively deploying **Trea Turner** (71.18) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (70.81); **Trea Turner** benefits from the favorable SP_xERA of 4.62, while **Pete Crow-Armstrong** earns a significant boost from dynamic platoon indicators. We are also expecting a breakout performance from **Colt Keith** (68.51); leading off against Ober presents a prime opportunity to capitalize on an elite 10% order bonus and a 7% platoon advantage, offsetting the minor drag from Ober's base-stealing prevention.\n\nConversely, our decision to bench **Josh Smith** (41.35) remains the most critical optimization choice of the morning. While he holds a strong platoon advantage against Woo, his lower base projection and the unfavorable eighth-spot in the order kept him just below the threshold required to displace starters like **Dillon Dingler** or **Carson Benge**. Risk remains centered on **Kazuma Okamoto** (42.20) and **Christian Yelich** (55.18), who are both facing significant challenges; **Kazuma Okamoto** must contend with an elite 2.67 xERA from Ohtani, while **Christian Yelich** faces a headwind (-5%) and a sub-3.30 xERA from Gray, dampening what would otherwise be a robust start. We will monitor the weather reports for the **Caleb Durbin** start, as the -5% wind impact could further suppress his ceiling despite a highly favorable matchup against the 10.13 xERA of Drohan.",
